When you want to reset the lab and “start from scratch” 

You must doe the following:

Vault container ✅
Vault volumes ✅
Vault data directory (./data) ✅ ← THIS is the key

 Note: Vault stores initialization state in the data directory





Step 1 — Full reset 

run this from your project root folder which is the **vault-troubleshooting-lab** directory.

docker compose down -v
docker rm -f vault-lab 2>/dev/null || true
docker system prune -f
docker network prune -f

Command	Purpose
docker-compose down -v	stops + removes containers & volumes
rm -rf data/*	deletes Vault storage (removes initialization)



Resetting the Lab
To reset everything
```
docker-compose down -v  #reset vault (Important)
rm -rf data/* init.txt setup/roles/app-role-id.txt setup/roles/app-secret-id.txt
     Vault is only initiated once, so to start over you need to delete the data directory.  
docker-compose up -d
vault status
```
At this point Vault will not be **initialized** and will be **sealed**.

